{
  "answer": "**The precise opening verse (first *sher*, or couplet) of *Diwan-e-Ghalib* chapter 1 (\"Aa ke meri jaan ko qarar nahin hai\") is:**\n\n> آ کہ مری جان کو قرار نہیں ہے  \n> طاقت_بیداد_انتظار نہیں ہے[^1]\n\nThis is from the original Urdu text (Arabic script). For reference:\n\n- **Transliteration**: Aa ke meri jaan ko qarar nahin hai / Taaqat-e-bidaad-e-intezar nahin hai.[^2]\n- **Translation**: My soul is free from comfort, free from care, / The strength to face this wait of deep despair is not there.[^3]\n\n[^1]: Mirza Ghalib, *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, ch. 1, [p-8d955a](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/01-aa-ke-meri-jaan-ko-qarar-nahin-hai/original/#p-8d955a).\n\n[^2]: <em>Ibid.</em>, transliteration variant (first verse after frontmatter).\n\n[^3]: <em>Ibid.</em>, translation variant, [p-8c8b08](/works/mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c/01-aa-ke-meri-jaan-ko-qarar-nahin-hai/translation/#p-8c8b08).",
